The paper deals with algorithms for constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs) and their application to 3-SAT, which is a well-studied problem in computer science. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deterministic local search, which is a common technique in the field of theoretical computer science, indicating that it could also be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper's focus on improving worst-case running time suggests that it could be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category, which often deals with optimization problems.
